text.tspan: After an Australian vessel, Ocean Shield, again detected deep-sea signals
consistent with those from an airplane’s black box, the official leading a
multination search expressed hope Wednesday that crews will begin to find
wreckage of a missing Malaysian airliner “within a matter of days.”
“I believe we’re searching in the right area,” Retired Air Chief Marshal Angus
All commercial transport aircraft are fitted with underwater locator beacons
to assist in the relocation of black box flight data recorders and cockpit voice
recorders. These beacons are free-running pingers that transmit signals at an
acoustic frequency of 37.5 kilohertz and have an expected battery life of 30
days. The scale of the challenge in locating the black boxes is immense.
